article.headline: Utah St. 90, S. Utah 57
article.story: LOGAN, Utah -- Jarred Shaw scored 24 points and grabbed 10 rebounds to lead Utah State to a 90-57 drubbing of Southern Utah on Tuesday night. Spencer Butterfield added 11 points for USU (2-0). The visiting Thunderbirds (1-1) were led by Trey Kennedy with 11. SUU's leading scorer, A.J. Hess was scoreless. USU burst out to a quick lead behind 13 first-half points from Shaw. Five consecutive points by reserve JoJo McGlaston gave the Aggies a 26-15 edge with 11:05 to play. Moments later, Butterfield nailed a 3-point shot as the result of an in-bounds play to give USU its first 20-plus-point lead of the game 36-15. USU led 46-26 at halftime. The Aggies had 32 points in the paint while SUU had 10. A combined 43 fouls were called in the game. USU head coach Stew Morrill has won 28 in a row at home against in-state teams.
